<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-780-621  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 780 621.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Dec 10 1990 v219 n25 p12(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Bellcore patent fights computer crime. (time-stamping forelectronic documents)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Warr, Michael.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Scott Stornetta and Stuart Haber, both employees of Bellcore, havepatented a means to time-stamp electronic documents in an attemptto prevent illegal tampering.andP;  The technology would prevent thealtering of dates on documents, assist in legal copyright datedisputes, and prevent the retouching of digital photographs.andO;Certain Bell companies are considering offering time-stampingservices, should it be allowed by the courts.andP;  To prevent anemployee from backdating a document, or making a tampered documentlook like the original, the patented system would linktime-stamped receipts sequentially.andP;  The patent process isexpected to take up to a year and a half to complete.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Bellcore Bell Communications Research Inc. (Officials andemployees).andO;Topic:     Legal IssuesComputer crimesPatentNew TechniqueFuture of ComputingTelephone companies.andO;Person:    Stornetta, Scott (Patents); Haber, Stuart (Patents).andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>